    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "* 10. Split into cases.\n\nAt times, you need to make a case distinction in your proof, as in the following example."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "Lemma example_cases : \n  ∀ x : ℝ, ∀ y : ℝ,\n    Rmax x y = x ∨ Rmax x y = y."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "Proof. \nTake x : ℝ. Take y : ℝ."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "text": "We now make a case distinction."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "text": "\nEither (x < y) or (x ≥ y).\n- Case (x < y).\n  It suffices to show that (Rmax x y = y).\n  By Rmax_right we conclude that (Rmax x y = y).\n- Case (x ≥ y).\n  It suffices to show that (Rmax x y = x).\n  By Rmax_left we conclude that (Rmax x y = x).\nQed."
    },
    {
